        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 18 at 4:29PM CDT until May 18 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Wichita KS</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Hesston, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated. At 428 PM CDT, ping pong ball sized hail
was reported in Hesston.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect damage
to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Hesston, Hillsboro, North Newton, Moundridge, Canton, Goessel,
Lehigh, and Marion Lake.

This includes Interstate 135 between Mile Markers 35 and 48.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
